Cell clustering of the RL lineage

Load packages

Load Seurat-allCell object

cdS <- readRDS(file = "Seurat_allCells.rds")
cdS <- UpdateSeuratObject(cdS)
cdS@ident <- factor(cdS@ident, ordered = F)
cell.ids <- c(4,6,10,12,11)
cdSsub <- SubsetData(cdS, ident.use = cell.ids, subset.raw = T)
# Inspect the selected cluster
p1 <- DimPlot(cdS, do.return = T, no.legend = T, do.label = T, reduction.use = "tsne")
p2 <- DimPlot(cdSsub, do.return = T, no.legend = T, do.label = T, reduction.use = "tsne")
plot_grid(p1,p2)

cdSsub <- NormalizeData(object = cdSsub, normalization.method = "LogNormalize", 
                      scale.factor = 10000)

We used URD to recluster the cells

We found that Seurat clustering does not work very well for small data set. We switched to URD. Through DE gene analysis, we found that cluster 4 was actually Purkinje cells. Thereefore, we removed this group for further analysis.

library(URD);
cdS <- readRDS("./data/Seurat_RL.rds")
cdS <- SubsetData(cdS, ident.remove = 4, subset.raw = T)
urd <- seuratToURD(cdS)
[1] "Marchenko-Pastur eigenvalue null upper bound: 2.22545018201863"
[1] "30 PCs have larger eigenvalues."
urd <- findVariableGenes(urd, cells.fit = NULL, set.object.var.genes = T,
                         diffCV.cutoff = 0.5, mean.min = 0.005, mean.max = 100, main.use = "",
                         do.plot = T)
length(urd@var.genes)
[1] 367

Visulize cell clustering with UMAP

We transfered the URD object back to Seurat, and used the RunUMAP function to plot cells in UMAP.

urd <- readRDS("./data/urd_RL.rds")
cdS.urd <- cdS.RL
cdS.urd@data <- urd@logupx.data
cdS.urd@dr$pca@cell.embeddings <- as.matrix(urd@pca.scores)
# Transfer the ident
ident <- urd@group.ids$ident
names(ident) <- names(cdS.urd@ident)
cdS.urd@ident <- as.factor(ident)
cdS.urd1 <- SubsetData(cdS.urd, ident.remove = 10, subset.raw = T)
cdS.urd1 <- RunUMAP(cdS.urd1, cells.use = NULL, dims.use = 1:11, reduction.use = "pca",
                   genes.use = NULL, assay.use = "RNA", max.dim = 2L,
